reviews.text: A Cantonese restaurant with a view. I had a friendly dim-sum gathering here on July 10, 2019. The food was so good that I must frequent this chain again!
Food is good, but the stage too low for ppl in the backseat to watch the show
Good food and decent service.  The seafood is really fresh.  Prices are reasonable.

The food is great, but took away too long to serve. We started at 8-ish PM, finish at about 11:30 PM for a total of 8 or 9 dishes, the last 3 plus dessert came in the last 10 mins together. The first couple dishes had a wait time of over 30 mins each, and there's over 1 hour gap in the middle that we simply sat at an empty table waiting.
nice place for Chinese food
